        "source_authority": "Kentucky Legislative Research Commission",
        "source_note": "Official current codified section. KRS 141.020(2)(f) states that for taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, the individual income tax is 3.5 percent of net income. This intake preserves the complete section and certifies only that statutory rate and effective period; it does not certify a complete final-return calculation.",
